course_metadata.title: Development of properties of building materials and computational applications

content_chunks.content: This course is a combination of e-course with online materials and hands on activities producing and testing a newly designed building material. The new building material partly consist of recycled materials. The testing in laboratory is done in teams. The tasks for teams follow CDIO principles.

Building materials development technology for sustainable construction - this course delivers practical methodologies for designing, producing, and testing innovative building materials with recycled content integration. Technology for material property development includes comprehensive property criteria selection and mass production optimization techniques for scalable building material manufacturing. The course introduces laboratory material production protocols and material testing procedures for comprehensive performance evaluation and quality assurance. Participants gain expertise in statistical analysis tools for determining declarable property values and performance assessment methodologies for building material certification. The curriculum covers recycled building materials integration strategies, computational material applications for performance prediction, and CDIO principles for systematic innovation development. Students develop hands-on experience in material design cycles, batch production testing, and performance validation through team-based laboratory activities. The course prepares professionals to develop sustainable building materials, implement quality control processes, and leverage computational tools for material optimization in circular economy construction applications.

content_chunks.title: Choosing the right criterion for a property of building material
Basics of mass production of materials
Using statistical tools to determine declarable values
Using statistical tools to assess whether measured values meet declared performance
